node.text:
The past year has challenged us all and sadly tragedy strikes again. Right in our back yard, many have had their lives change in a second. Let’s continue to show our strength and support where ever we can. My sweet friends at Global Empowerment Mission (GEM) have stepped up in a variety of ways to ease the burden and provide aid. I will stand with them and help in anyway possible. If you have a desire to help please see the various areas of need for the families in the Champlain building collapse in Miami. 

GEM in partnership with BStrong has assisted over 17 families
$25,500 in gift cards has been given out so far
GEM/Bstrong gift cards that are being handed out are around $1500.00 each
We will need to provide assistance to over 200 people and over 400 first responders

REQUEST

AIRBNB or ANY HOMEOWNER IN THE MIAMI AREA: We need long term housing solutions for these displaced people, the survivors and first responders for a month or two.. 

RESTAURANTS: The first responders are in need of 400 hot meals per breakfast, lunch and dinner as they are doing search and rescue as well as recovery. Any portion of the effort that a restaurant can provide would be welcomed! 

GEM is in need of cash donations for gift cards at the following link..

https://www.globalempowermentmission.org/champlaintowerresidentsfund

If you would like to make an in-kind donation of goods we are in need of the following..
Healthy Snacks
Protein Bars
Non-Perishable goods

Please complete the following link so that they can provide you an in-kind donation letter for your tax deduction.
www.globalempowermentmission.org/inkinddonation
